ditions. Strassfeld refutes this story as he traces phenomenology’s reception in America, delivering the first systematic historical study of the movement in the United States. He examines the lives and works of Marjorie Grene, Alfred Schütz, Hubert Dreyfus, and Iris Marion Young, among others, while also providing a fresh introduction to phenomenological philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPhenomenologyxStudy and teachingzUnited States. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  acontinental philosophy, deconstruction, post-structuralism, existentialism, intellectual movements, social theory, influence, academia, nonfiction, iris marion young, hubert dreyfus, alfred schutz, marjorie grene, analytic, maurice merleau-ponty, martin heidegger, edmund husserl, discourse, reception, academic institutions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishz978311099276208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022z9783110992755oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665090 cprintz978022682157340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226821580423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226821580/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099276-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPHb2022